    "content": "# 5 Ways to Fix Pragmata Controller Not Working PC Bug: Ultimate Troubleshooting Guide\n\nAre you experiencing frustrating controller issues while trying to play Pragmata on your PC? You're not alone. Many players have reported that their gamepads simply won't respond, making it impossible to enjoy this highly anticipated action-adventure title. In this comprehensive guide, we'll walk you through 5 proven methods to fix the Pragmata controller not working PC bug, so you can get back to exploring the dark fantasy world without missing a beat.\n\nBefore we dive into the fixes, let's take a moment to understand what makes Pragmata such a compelling experience—and why getting your controller working is absolutely essential.\n\n## What Makes Pragmata Special?\n\nPragmata is an epic open-world action RPG set in a dark fantasy realm. Developed by Monolith Productions and published by Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment, this critically acclaimed title (Metacritic Score: 83) immerses players in a vast, hand-crafted world teeming with danger and intrigue. As a lone warrior, you must navigate treacherous landscapes, battle fearsome creatures, and unravel the mysteries of a forgotten civilization.\n\nIf you're a fan of Massively Multiplayer, RPG games, you'll find plenty to love in Pragmata's deep combat system and character customization. For those seeking similar experiences, check out [best Massively Multiplayer, RPG games](https://pcgamearchive.com/en/game/x) that offer comparable depth and immersion.\n\n## Key Features That Make Pragmata Unforgettable\n\n### Vast Open World\nExplore a sprawling world filled with dynamic weather, day-night cycles, and hidden secrets. Every corner of the map offers something unique, from ancient ruins to bustling towns.\n\n### Deep Combat System\nEngage in visceral, skill-based combat with a variety of weapons and magic. Master timing, dodges, and combos to overcome challenging foes.\n\n### Character Customization\nCreate a hero tailored to your playstyle with extensive skill trees, armor sets, and weapon choices. Your decisions shape your abilities and appearance.\n\n### Gripping Narrative\nUnravel a complex story filled with morally ambiguous choices. Your actions influence the world and its inhabitants, leading to multiple endings.\n\n### Dynamic World Events\nExperience a living world where NPCs have their own schedules, and random events can alter your journey.\n\n## Gameplay Overview\n\nPragmata combines action-packed combat with deep RPG mechanics. Players can explore freely, taking on quests, crafting gear, or simply discovering hidden lore. The game rewards both strategic planning and quick reflexes, offering a balanced challenge for all playstyles.\n\nThe world reacts to your choices, making each playthrough unique. Form alliances, betray friends, or remain a lone wolf—every decision has consequences. Fans of Action, Adventure games will appreciate the fluid combat and exploration mechanics. If this sounds appealing, you might also enjoy [best Action, Adventure games](https://pcgamearchive.com/en/game/blade-bones) like *Blade & Bones*, which offers similar dynamic combat and rich storytelling.\n\n## 5 Ways to Fix Pragmata Controller Not Working PC Bug\n\nNow let's tackle the main issue. Here are five proven methods to resolve controller problems in Pragmata:\n\n### 1. Update Your Controller Drivers and Windows\n\nOutdated drivers are the most common cause of controller issues. Follow these steps:\n\n- Press Windows + X and select Device Manager\n- Expand Human Interface Devices and Universal Serial Bus controllers\n- Right-click your controller and select Update driver\n- Check for Windows updates via Settings > Update & Security\n\n### 2. Disable Steam Input Override\n\nSteam's controller configuration can conflict with Pragmata's native support:\n\n- Open Steam and go to Library\n- Right-click Pragmata and select Properties\n- Under Controller, set \"Steam Input Per-Game Setting\" to Disable\n- Launch the game and test your controller\n\n### 3. Run the Game in Windowed Mode\n\nSome players report that borderless windowed mode fixes controller detection:\n\n- Navigate to Pragmata's settings file (usually in `Documents/My Games/Pragmata`)\n- Open `config.ini` and change `Fullscreen=1` to `Fullscreen=0`\n- Save and restart the game\n\n### 4. Use a Third-Party Controller Emulator\n\nTools like DS4Windows (for PlayStation controllers) or x360ce can translate your controller signals:\n\n- Download and install DS4Windows\n- Configure your controller profile\n- Launch the emulator before starting Pragmata\n\n### 5. Verify Game File Integrity\n\nCorrupted game files can cause input issues:\n\n- Open Steam library\n- Right-click Pragmata > Properties > Local Files\n- Click Verify integrity of game files\n- Wait for the process to complete and restart\n\nIf these fixes don't resolve the issue, you might want to explore other Action, RPG games that offer similar immersive experiences without controller headaches. For instance, [best Action, RPG games](https://pcgamearchive.com/en/game/forgotten-realms-demon-stone) like *Forgotten Realms: Demon Stone* provide engaging gameplay with excellent controller support.\n\n## System Requirements for Pragmata\n\nTo ensure smooth gameplay, make sure your PC meets these requirements:\n\nMinimum:\n- OS: Windows 7/8/10 64-bit\n- Processor: Intel Core i5-2500K or AMD FX-8320\n- Memory: 6 GB RAM\n- Graphics: NVIDIA GeForce GTX 660 or AMD Radeon HD 7870\n- DirectX: Version 11\n- Storage: 45 GB available space\n\nRecommended:\n- OS: Windows 10 64-bit\n- Processor: Intel Core i7-3770 or AMD Ryzen 5 1600\n- Memory: 8 GB RAM\n- Graphics: NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1060 or AMD Radeon RX 580\n- DirectX: Version 11\n- Storage: 45 GB available space\n\n## Why You Should Play Pragmata\n\nEven with minor technical hiccups, Pragmata delivers one of the most compelling action RPG experiences of the past decade. The deep combat system, meaningful choices, and breathtaking world make it a must-play for any fan of the genre. If you enjoy Massively Multiplayer, RPG games, you'll find that Pragmata's solo adventure scratches a similar itch with its rich customization and emergent storytelling.\n\nFor those who appreciate epic space operas, [best Massively Multiplayer, RPG games](https://pcgamearchive.com/en/game/star-wars) like *STAR WARS* titles offer a different flavor of immersive role-playing with equally deep mechanics.\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe Pragmata controller not working PC bug can be frustrating, but these five solutions should get you back in action quickly. Start with the simplest fixes—driver updates and Steam Input settings—before moving to more advanced troubleshooting.\n\nDon't let a minor technical issue keep you from experiencing one of the finest open-world RPGs available. With an 83 Metacritic score and a world that genuinely reacts to your choices, Pragmata is an adventure worth fighting for.\n\nReady to dive in? Try these fixes, grab your controller, and prepare for an unforgettable journey through a dark fantasy realm where your every decision shapes the story. The world of Pragmata awaits!"
